transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Customer Service, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, how are you doing?

Speaker 1: Listen, I got a prescription, I don't know, a few weeks back.

Speaker 2: I just got another one yesterday.

Speaker 1: I no longer need the prescription anymore,

Speaker 2: and I didn't know that they were going to keep sending it to me every

Speaker 1: whatever, so many weeks.

Speaker 2: I'd like to cancel this prescription so they don't keep charging me.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let me pull up your account.

Speaker 1: Can I have your name and birthday?

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name is Silvio Polini, and my birthday is 10-12-1960.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 1: Alrighty, I'm just going to pause out your account so that your

Speaker 2: prescription stays active with the doctor, but you won't get any monthlies.

Speaker 1: You can call in to place an order.

Speaker 2: No, I don't need it anymore.

Speaker 1: I won't be needing it.

Speaker 2: You can just cancel me right now.

Speaker 1: I won't be calling you ever again.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: I went ahead and canceled you out.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.
